Key Match Events: Pakistan won by 7 wickets (with 5 balls remaining)
Babar Azam got out for 53 off 42 balls
Mohammad Rizwan got out for 67 off 36 balls
Haris Rauf and Mohammad Haris scored 10 and 14 respectively
Post-Match Reflections: Pakistan were outstanding in the last six overs, allowing just 53 runs off those 36 deliveries
Pakistan dominated with the bat, racing through the powerplay, crashing 55 runs in those six overs
Pakistan were better with the ball, better in the field as well
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Sydney Cricket Ground
The match was the 1st semi-final of the ICC Men's T20 World Cup 2022-11-09
